<li class="comment odd score8" id="comment-1408794">
<h2>

<a class="anchor" href="/users/unixjunkie/journaux/vlc-passe-a-la-lgpl#comment-1408794" title="Lien direct vers ce commentaire">#</a>
 
<a class="title" href="/nodes/96425/comments/1408794">Un mini-message plus qu&#39;un journal</a>
</h2>
<p class="meta">
Posté par <a href="/users/antistress" rel="author">antistress</a> (<a href="http://libre-ouvert.toile-libre.org/">page perso</a>) <time class="updated" datetime="2012-11-15T14:09:59+01:00"><span class="date">le 15/11/12</span> <span class="time">à 14:09</span></time>.
Évalué à&nbsp;<span class="score">
8
</span>.<span class="update">
Dernière modification : le 15/11/12 à 14:12
</span></p>
<figure class="image"><img alt="" class="avatar" height="64" src="//img.linuxfr.org/avatars/033/055/000/avatar.png" width="64" /></figure>
<div class="content">
<p>J'aurais bien aimé lire dans le journal quelle était la licence jusqu'alors et pourquoi le changement de licence.</p>

<p>Le 1er lien donné indique :</p>

<blockquote>
<p>As you might know, or might have read, I am spending a lot of my time to relicense libVLC, aka VLC engine, from GPL to LGPL.</p>

<p>There are quite a few good reasons to do so, some more obvious than others, but notably competition, necessity to have more professional developers around VLC and AppStores. Other reasons also exist, but this is not the place and time to discuss those.</p>
</blockquote>

<p>C'est très flou.</p>
</div>
<footer class="actions">
</footer>

